{
  "texts": [
    "The proposed DNN outperformed the other baseline models, achieving a prediction accuracy of 97.5%.",
    "A self-attention mechanism and depth matrix decomposition were integrated into the student performance prediction model using DNNs, the model suggested by Yang and Bai (2022) is called (Factorization Deep Product Neural network, FDPN).",
    "The FDPN model fully learns the relationship between the features and scores, which improves the prediction effect of the model in comparison with using only single feature learning.",
    "In addition, the model, which used a factorization machine and two different types of neural networks, considered the influence of first-order features, second-order features, and high-order features simultaneously.",
    "Moreover, as the model was combination-based, it combined the student demographics, course, and learning behavior features obtained from the learning analysis dataset containing 412 courses with 600 students, which was used to assess the model's performance."
  ]
}